CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1774444274
OL,3,CHouseholds could face 8% jump in food
OL,4,Cprices due to Iran war, experts warn
OL,6,FThis would add more than #150 to the
OL,7,Faverage household's annual grocery
OL,8,Fbill and add further pressure on
OL,9,Ffamily budgets already preparing for a
OL,10,Fjump in energy bills this summer.
OL,12,FFood production is energy intensive
OL,13,Fand therefore particularly exposed to
OL,14,Fsudden changes in oil and gas prices,
OL,15,Fas has been witnessed in recent weeks.
OL,17,FThe latest modelling shows that a
OL,18,Fmiddle scenario with a "more moderate"
OL,19,Fenergy shock would still lift average
OL,20,Ffood inflation to around 4.8% for 2026.
OL,26,@zD@XOUzD@fO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
