OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1774444274
OL,3,CHouseholds could face 8% jump in food
OL,4,Cprices due to Iran war, experts warn
OL,6,FA baseline scenario with no Middle
OL,7,FEast conflict would still see food
OL,8,Finflation averaging 3.8% for the year.
OL,10,FJames Walton, chief economist at IGD,
OL,11,Fsaid: "Even in the best case scenario,
OL,12,Fthe conflict in the Middle East is
OL,13,Flikely to prolong the timeline for
OL,14,Frecovery from the cost-of-living
OL,15,Fcrisis.
OL,17,F"Persistently high food prices
OL,18,Fcontinue to fuel concern over excess
OL,19,Fprofits, based on the assumption that
OL,20,Fhigher prices must mean higher profits
OL,21,Ffor food businesses.
OL,26,@sD@GOUyD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
